                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25844",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As the second parameter is optional I suggest setting $name = null and verifying whether $name === null to be conform with \"PHP Coding Standard (draft) -> Optional Parameters\".\n\nOne more thing: if name is given you're currently adding two spaces between name and email address. A possible variant, IMO also easier to read could be:\n\n{noformat}\npublic function setFrom($email, $name = null)\n{\n    if ($this->_from === null) {\n        $email = strtr($email,\"\\r\\n\\t\",'???');\n        $this->_from = $email;\n\n        if (null === $name) {\n            $from = sprintf('\"%s\" ', $this->_encodeHeader($name));\n        } else {\n            $from = '';\n        }\n        $from .= sprintf('<%s>', (string) $email);\n        $this->_storeHeader('From', $from, true);\n    } else {\n        ...\n{noformat}\n\nCheers,\nThomas\n\nSorry for nitpicking, could not resist ;-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-07T08:46:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-07T08:46:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25865",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "name": "yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "displayName": "old of Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hello, Thomas.\nYou are welcome.;-)   Thank You for Your advice. \n\nI refixed as following.\n\n1) If $name is not used or the $name is same as $email,\n        header is \"From: $email\".\n\n2) If $name is used and the $name is encoded,\n        header is \"From: $name <$email>\".\n\n3) If $name is used and the $name is not encoded and not contains comma, \n        header is \"From: $name <$email>\".\n\n4) If $name is used and the $name is not encoded and contains comma, \n        header is \"From: \"$name\" <$email>\".\n\nBest Regards,\nSatoru Yoshida",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "name": "yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "displayName": "old of Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-07T10:51:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-07T10:51:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25885",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Great. One last note: Wouln't 1) better be From: <$email> ?\n\nRegards,\nThomas Gelf\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
